[
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="81">BRAZIL</emphasis>
?]. 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="81">Bartlett s. n.</emphasis>
(W).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="21" lastPageNumber="82" pageId="20" pageNumber="81" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageId="20" pageNumber="81">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="82">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alston ex Crabbe &amp; Jermy" authorityYear="1973" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella palmiformis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="palmiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">
<pageBreakToken pageId="21" pageNumber="82" start="start">Selaginella</pageBreakToken>
palmiformis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a member of subg. 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="(Stachygynandrum)" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Stachygynandrum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Stachygynandrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is characterized by its usually 1-pinnate branches that look like miniature palm leaves. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B1" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany 9 (4): 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
this species was restricted to the Sierras of the Amazonian part of Venezuela and Colombia; however, 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, AR" journalOrPublisher="Sida" pageId="24" pageNumber="85" pagination="2321 - 2342" refId="B25" refString="Smith, AR, Leon, B, Tuomisto, H, van der Werff, H, Moran, RC, Lehnert, M, Kessler, M, 2005. New records of pteridophytes for the flora of Peru. Sida 21: 2321 - 2342" title="New records of pteridophytes for the flora of Peru." volume="21" year="2005">Smith et al. (2005)</bibRefCitation>
recorded it in the Department of Loreto, Peru at 100-200 m and here we registered it in Amazonas Department of that country, where it was collected at 680 m. Both Departments are located in the Peruvian Amazon region. We also confirm the distribution range of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alston ex Crabbe &amp; Jermy" authorityYear="1973" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella palmiformis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="palmiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella palmiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to include the states of Acre and Amazonas in Brazil. It can be surmised that this species is widespread in the Amazon River basin in South America and that it grows in lowland tropical rainforests and in premontane wet forests from 100 to 1000 m.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="82">
<bibRefCitation author="Alston, AHG" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany" pageId="23" pageNumber="84" pagination="233 - 330" refId="B1" refString="Alston, AHG, Jermy, AC, Rankin, JM, 1981. The genus Selaginella in tropical South America. Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Botany 9 (4): 233 - 330" title="The genus Selaginella in tropical South America." volume="9" year="1981">Alston et al. (1981)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bautista" authorityYear="1974" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella manausensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="manausensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella manausensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella bahiensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Spring (= 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jermy &amp; J. M. Rankin" authorityYear="1981" baseAuthorityName="Bautista" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella bahiensis subsp. manausensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="bahiensis" subSpecies="manausensis">Selaginella bahiensis subsp. manausensis</taxonomicName>
). As part of his ongoing monographic work on the &quot; 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella flabellata" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="flabellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella flabellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Spring group&quot; the senior author studied the types of 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella bahiensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[BRAZIL. Bahia: In vicinia urbis Soteropoleos, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Blanchet 2528</emphasis>
(holotype: G!; isotypes: photo BM!, G!, P-2 sheets!], 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bautista" authorityYear="1974" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella manausensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="manausensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella manausensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alston ex Crabbe &amp; Jermy" authorityYear="1973" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella palmiformis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="palmiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella palmiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Based on this we conclude that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bautista" authorityYear="1974" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella manausensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="manausensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella manausensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not closely related to 
<taxonomicName class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella bahiensis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="bahiensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella bahiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but rather it is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alston ex Crabbe &amp; Jermy" authorityYear="1973" class="Lycopodiopsida" family="Selaginellaceae" genus="Selaginella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Selaginella palmiformis" order="Selaginellales" pageId="21" pageNumber="82" phylum="Lycopodiophyta" rank="species" species="palmiformis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="82">Selaginella palmiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and, accordingly, it is synonymized here.
</paragraph>
